    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Certificates attesting that a thing or things are of the location of origin, provenance, creator, date, or materials which are claimed; signatures of officials or official seals are often included on the certificate to verify the claim. Examples include certificates of authenticity for art works, artifacts, memorabilia, collectibles, and software.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
